         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nMesoamerican numbers were used in a chronological system, as evidenced by archaeological findings (<htcite0>; <htcite1>; <htcite2>). As a result, we cannot perform calculations with them in the same way we do with our numbers, nor as in the *\"Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay\"*, method, developed and published by Dhavit Prem of the *Associação Yupanki* (<htcite3>; <htcite4>).\n\nHowever, the fact that we cannot use them in the same way does not mean we cannot apply our knowledge to infer how they might have been used. With this in mind, we invite you to reflect:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e",
                     "text": "Catepillán, Ximena",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
