      {
         "id": "SECTION_sum",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Adding an Order\n\nJust as we have done throughout this section, we will begin with only one order, known by the Maya as the *K'iin* (equivalent to our units, but representing days) (<htcite0>; <htcite1>), expanding our knowledge as we progress through the text.\n\nTo carry out the addition of Mesoamerican numbers, we will use the algorithms proposed by Ruy D. Díaz (<htcite2>). Since we do not know the symbols that Indigenous peoples used to represent addition and equality, we will adapt these operations by using the current symbols for addition (+) and equality (=).\n\nIn this first stage, we present a small table (Calculation 1) in which it is possible to modify the values using the side arrows. The final result will always change within the permitted range, from 0 to 19. If the value exceeds the minimum or maximum limit, the page will automatically adjust the other value, respecting the established limits:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ad11b3b2-8cdf-4d71-9cb7-2ac241850945",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí.",
                     "page": "pp. 34",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eca99877-c520-4569-a71c-0a5b3dd77dc4",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí.",
                     "page": "pp. 34",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "9e7d0cea-d968-4bd5-886e-bc08c824e7ca",
                     "text": "Díaz, Ruy D.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2006",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"oneOrder\" class=\"tableTen\"><tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Left Control</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Value</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Addition Sign</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Value</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Equals Sign</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Result</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Right Control</b></td></tr>  <tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeUpL\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeDownL\"></i></td><td><img id=\"imgml0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgml0', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_19.png\" /></td><td> + </td><td><img id=\"imgmr0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgmr0', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_0.png\" /></td><td> = </td><td><img id=\"imgme0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgme0', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_19.png\" /></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeUpR\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeDownR\"></i> </td></tr>  <tr><td><span id=\"leftVL0\">19</span></td><td> + </td><td><span id=\"rightVR0\">0</span></td><td> = </td><td><span id=\"totalVE0\">19</span></td></tr></table></p><p class=\"desc\">Calculation 1: Addition of numbers whose maximum result is 19.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_one_more_order",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Adding Two Orders\n\nThe second numerical order of the Mesoamericans is known by the Maya as *Winal* (corresponding to our tens, but understood as \"the person\") (<htcite0>; <htcite1>). This order follows the pattern of a vigesimal system, meaning that any number placed in this position represents the number multiplied by 20.\n\nBefore continuing, let’s see how we write the number 25 using the decimal and chronological numerical orders already explored in the previous text (<htcite2>):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "ad11b3b2-8cdf-4d71-9cb7-2ac241850945",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí.",
                     "page": "pp. 34",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eca99877-c520-4569-a71c-0a5b3dd77dc4",
                     "text": "Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí.",
                     "page": "pp. 34",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2022",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "1388be6c-13c5-47a8-b945-56020b798c5f",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Calendários mesoamericanos",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p style=\"text-align=center\"><p><math display=\"block\">  <mo>a)</mo> <mn>25</mn> = <mo>(</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>10</mn><mo>) + </mo> <mo>(</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>)</mo> </math></p><p style=\"text-align=center\"><p><math display=\"block\">  <mo>b)</mo> <mn>25</mn> = <mo>(</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>20</mn><mo>) + </mo> <mo>(</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>)</mo> </math></p><p class=\"desc\">Calculation 2: Rewriting the number 25, making the numerical orders explicit in decimal base (a) and chronological base (b).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### Adding Within Limits\n\nNext, we perform the sum 25 + 25 using decimal numbers and Mesoamerican numbers. In the Mesoamerican case, we follow the algorithm proposed by Ruy D. Díaz (<htcite0>). It is worth noting that, since none of the orders contain values greater than 19, no additional adjustments are necessary:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "9e7d0cea-d968-4bd5-886e-bc08c824e7ca",
                     "text": "Díaz, Ruy D.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2006",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p style=\"text-align=center\"><center>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmoc2\">1 </span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmtc2\">2</span><span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmtc1\">5</span> <br />+&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmbc2\">2</span><span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmbc1\">5 </span><br />____________<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmrc2\">5</span><span class=\"sumexample1\" id=\"cmrc1\">0 </span></center></p><p class=\"desc\">Calculation 3: Addition of 25 + 25.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"twoOrders\" class=\"tableTen\"><tr><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Value</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Addition Sign</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Value</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Equal Sign</b></td><td style=\"background-color: lightblue\"><b>Result</b></td></tr> <tr><td><img id=\"imgml1\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgml1', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td rowspan=\"2\"> + </td><td><img id=\"imgmr2\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgmr2', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_2.png\" /></td><td rowspan=\"2\"> = </td><td><img id=\"imgme3\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgme3', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_4.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img id=\"imgml4\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgml4', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_5.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgmr5\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgmr5', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_5.png\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgme6\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgme6', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Maya_10.png\" /></td></tr>   <tr><td><span id=\"leftVL1\">25</span></td><td> + </td><td><span id=\"rightVR1\">25</span></td><td> = </td><td><span id=\"totalVE1\">50</span></td></tr></table></p><p class=\"desc\">Calculation 4: Addition of 25 + 25 using vigesimal numbers.</p>",
