            {
               "text": "#### Adjusting the Values\n\nWhen a sum exceeds the values allowed in an order, adjustments must be made. In the *Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay*, method, Dhavit Prem proposes five adjustments, presented in **Table 1** (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).\n\nFor decimal numbers, the excess value is carried over to the next order, as in **Calculation 3**. In contrast, in the Mesoamerican system, Ruy D. Díaz suggests first performing the addition horizontally and then applying the adjustments (<htcite2>).\n\nTo illustrate, let’s add 19 + 19:",
